  {
    "client_msg_id": "5c8ac0cb-a28e-4a0e-b83b-80ec2f0a4b67",
    "type": "message",
    "text": "Thanks for reading!\n\n8 is just saying I don't design for the code to be behind a pane of glass that others won't modify. That's it.\n\nThe reorganizations were point 5, and they're definitely C-focused. Auto-generating headers is a level of spoonfeeding that no other language needs.\n\n6 is for trying to help others grok my codebases. Giving them some way to stage their learning rather than throwing them into the maximum-complexity state right from the start.",
